{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Ban multiple interviews for jobs paying under \u00a315p/h & prioritise UC claimants",
        "additional_details": "Many companies are hosting multiple interview rounds for basic wage jobs. We think this wastes interviewee time and where that individual is on UC, government funds. Many people applying for those roles are willing to get back into work ASAP, and able to do the role, that\u2019s all that\u2019s necessary for those roles. \u00a315 an hour is above minimum wage but we think a fair threshold and helps those willing to take any role, even if they\u2019re over qualified, because they want to work, pay their bills, and carry out their normal life.",
        "background": "Make a law that companies hiring for roles paying under \u00a315 an hour can\u2019t hold more than one interview round, and must prioritise those currently on Universal Credit. All jobs under this threshold must be posted to JobCentre sites.",
